text: Carallia brachiata is a large tree in the family Rhizophoraceae, that grows to a height of 25 metres and found from Australia, Malesia, Indochina through to the Western Ghats. Its leaves are the food plant of the moth Dysphania percota. C. brachiata inflorescence Dysphania percota larva on a leaf ==References== brachiata
title: Carallia brachiata
